'''
Multiple Alignment Solution
'''

'''
An alignment of three sequences requires the formation of a 3D scoring and backtrack matrix where the score of each
node is the maximum of all seven incoming edges plus the nodes from which the edges originate. Accounting for the
edge used to form the longest path to every node in the 3D scoring matrix allows for backtracking to form the alignment
of the three sequences.
'''


